description.narrative: Steady progress has been made in strengthening the child protection sector at regional level through engagement with partners organizations, such as the African Union, Intergovernmental Authority for Development, East African Community, UNHCR, IOM and Save the Children. Engagement of regional and sub-regional partners through various regional platforms has allowed ESARO to focus on and promote UNICEF's regional priorities of social service workforce strengthening, protection from sexual exploitation, addressing the adverse effects of migration, violence prevention and response, and programming on harmful practices. Engagement on emergency preparedness has advanced at country and regional level increasingly through multi-sectoral initiatives. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
